Date: Fri 24 Jul 2015
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly disease information 2015; 28(31) [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=18205


Sheep pox and goat pox, Kazakhstan
----------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 24 Jul 2015 from Dr Samat Tyulegenov, Deputy Director, RSE "National Reference Center for Veterinary", Ministry of Agriculture, Astana, Kazakhstan

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 10 Jul 2015
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 22 Jul 2015
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: March 2015
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Capripoxvirus
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks
Summary of outbreaks: Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak: Pervomaysk village, Akzhayik area, Kabyrshakty rural district, Ural 'Sk [West Kazakhstan region]
Date of start of the outbreak: 10 Jul 2015
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: village
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Sheep / 5061 / 80 / 0 / 0 / 0

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Sheep / 1.58 / 0 / 0 / 0
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: Quarantine measures were implemented on 13 Jul 2015.

Control measures
Measures applied: quarantine; movement control inside the country; vaccination in response to the outbreak(s); disinfection/disinfestations; dipping/spraying; no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: National Reference Center for Veterinary (regional reference laboratory)
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Sheep / agar-gel precipitation (AGP) test / 22 Jul 2015 / Positive
Sheep / real-time PCR / 22 Jul 2015 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[During 2015, Kazakhstan reported 2 events of sheep pox and goat pox. One was located in western Kazakhstan and the 2nd was located in eastern Kazakhstan.
See event summary and map of the western Kazakhstan outbreak at http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review/viewsummary?reportid=17224 and
event summary and map of the eastern Kazakhstan outbreak at
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review/viewsummary?reportid=17465.

This current event is the 2nd outbreak occurring in western Kazakhstan. - Mod.CRD]

[Map of showing neighboring countries
http://www.gezilecekyer.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Rusya-map-harita.jpg.
Both outbreaks are very close to the Russian border, but the eastern outbreak is close to where a northern extension of China juts between Kazakhstan & Mongolia. - Mod.JW]
